    <body>
        <h1 id="Heading">HTML Links - Hyperlinks</h1>

        <hr>

        <h2>HTML Links - Syntax</h2>
        <p>
            &lt;a&gt; tag defines a hyperlink.
        </p>
        <p>
            The Target attribute specifies where to open the linked document.
        </p>

        <h2>
            Different Target Attributes
        </h2>
        <p>
            The <a href="https://www.google.com/" target="_self">Self</a> Target Attribute opens the document in the same Window/Tab.<br>
            The <a href="https://www.google.com/" target="_blank">Blank</a> Target Attribute opens the document in a new Window or Tab.<br>
            The <a href="https://www.google.com/" target="_parent">Parent</a> Target Attribute opens the document in the Parent Frame.<br>
            The <a href="https://www.google.com/" target="_top">Top</a> Target Attribute opens the document in the Fullbody of the Window.<br>
        </p>

        <h2>
            Button as a Link.
        </h2>
        <p>
            The Button Tag is used to make Clickable Text Element on the Webpage.<br>
            <a href="https://www.google.com/"><button>This is a Button</button></a>
        </p>

        <h2>
            HTML Link Colours
        </h2>
        <p>
            The CSS for a Link allows us to define different state styles of the links.
        </p>

        <p>
            The <b>Link Style</b> defines the initial style of the Link.<br>
            The <b>Visited Style</b> defines the style of the Link after visiting it.<br>
            The <b>Hover Style</b> defines the style of the Link while hovering over it.<br>
            The <b>Active Style</b> defines the style of the Link while visiting it.<br>
        </p>

        <h2>
            HTML Bookmarks
        </h2>
        <p>
            The <b>HTML Bookmarks</b> are declared using the 'ID' attribute.<br>
            <a href="#Heading"><button>Scroll back to the Top</button></a>
        </p>

        <hr>

